{"lemma":"عِزُّ","slug":"عِزُّ","root":"ع.ز.ز","root_slug":"ع-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عِزّ","root":"عزز","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28909","n28916","n28917","n29027"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B2%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be powerful, to overpower"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be dear, to be precious, to be rare","examples":[{"text":"رَجُلٌ فِي زَمَنٍ عَزَّ فِيهِ ٱلرِّجَالُ","english":"a man at a time when real men are scarce"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَزَّ (ʕazza) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew עזז ('azáz, “to make strong”)."},"ipa":["/ʕaz.za/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28909","headword_ar":"عَزَّ","root":"Ez","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, A, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, S, K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazaAzapN","text_ar":"عَزَازَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, mighty, potent, powerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~z","text_ar":"تعزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made himself so; he strengthened himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaw~aY","text_ar":"تَقَوَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became so after being low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean, in condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, A, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazirota","text_ar":"عَزِرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated, in rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state; noble, honourable, glorious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"illustrious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, * K, * TK; and TA in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~z","text_ar":"تعزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * K, * TK.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a wajal~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ وَجَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", referring to the name of God expressed or understood, is a phrase of frequent occurrence, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To Him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to Whom, belong might and majesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glory and greatness."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazazotu Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَزَزْتُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K,) meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karumotu Ealayohi","text_ar":"كَرُمْتُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, *) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I exceeded him in nobleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazaAzapN","text_ar":"عَزَازَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He magnified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exalted, himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was disdainful, scornful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indignant, in a blamable manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; q. v. infrà.) [See also 5.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He resisted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withstood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was indomitable, invincible; not to be overcome."},{"kind":"text","text":"(B and TA, in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"عَزَّ الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotaz~a","text_ar":"اِعْتَزَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (occurring in the TA, coupled with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEas~ara","text_ar":"تَعَسَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manuEa","text_ar":"مَنُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnE","text_ar":"منع"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~z","text_ar":"تعزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impossible, insuperable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unattainable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or so, as Es-Sarakustee says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~z","text_ar":"تعزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazaAzapN","text_ar":"عَزَازَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, O, K, meaning anything, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rare, scarce, hardly to be found."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b6-  [And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, dear, highly esteemed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatly valued."},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a EalaY~a A^ano tafoEala","text_ar":"عَزَّ عَلَىَّ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Mgh, O, K,) [the second pers. of the pret. being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazazota","text_ar":"عَزَزْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazizota","text_ar":"عَزِزْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the latter aor. the more chaste, (O,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy doing so distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicted, me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, emphatically,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distresses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicts, me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otad~a","text_ar":"اِشْتَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~a","text_ar":"حَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~a","text_ar":"شَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) a phrase [often, but not always,] alluding to a loathing of the action, or indignation thereat. (Msb.) In like manner also you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a EalaY~a ka*aA","text_ar":"عَزَّ عَلَىَّ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a thing"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2031},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicted, me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a EalaY~a A^ano","text_ar":"عَزَّ عَلَىَّ اَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asuwo'aka","text_ar":"اَسُوْءَكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicted, me to displease thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a maA A^an~aka *aAhibN","text_ar":"عَزَّ مَا اَنَّكَ ذَاهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~a A^an~aka *aAhibN","text_ar":"حَقَّ اَنَّكَ ذَاهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~a maA An~k *Ahb","text_ar":"حَقَّ مَا انّك ذاهب"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is distressing that thou art going away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And one says to a man, Dost thou love me? and he replies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEaz~a maA","text_ar":"لَعَزَّ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"la$ad~a maA","text_ar":"لَشَدَّ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHaq~a maA","text_ar":"لَحَقَّ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It distresses"},{"kind":"text","text":"me, what thou sayest; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it has distressed me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA A^aSaAbaka","text_ar":"بِمَا اَصَابَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uEozizotu","text_ar":"اُعْزِزْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"am, distressed by what befell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath befallen, thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY~a bimaA A^uSibota bihi","text_ar":"عَلَىَّ بِمَا اُصِبْتَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozizo","text_ar":"اَعْزِزْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That by which thou hast been afflicted distresses me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how doth it distress me!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] so in a trad. of 'Alee; when he beheld Talhah slain, he said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY~a","text_ar":"عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozizo","text_ar":"اَعْزِزْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaA muHam~adK A^ano A^araAka mujad~alFA taHota nujuwmi Als~amaA='i","text_ar":"اَبَا مُحَمَّدٍ اَنْ اَرَاكَ مُجَدَّلًا تَحْتَ نُجُومِ السَّمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It distresses me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how doth it distress me! O Aboo-Mohammad, that I see thee prostrated upon the ground beneath the stars of heaven"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [A similar ex. is given in the A; without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano","text_ar":"اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, weak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus having two contr. meanings. (Msb.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~ahu","text_ar":"عَزَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~N","text_ar":"عَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conquered him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he overcame him in argumentative contest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazoEazahu","text_ar":"عَزْعَزَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EazoEazapN","text_ar":"عَزْعَزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~ahu fiY AlxiTaAbi","text_ar":"عَزَّهُ فِى الخِطَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Jel in xxxviii. 22, and TA:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became stronger than he therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he strove with him to overcome therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAz~hu","text_ar":"عازّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAz~apN","text_ar":"مُعَازَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA:) in the Kur xxxviii. 22, some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~aniY","text_ar":"عَزَّنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and others, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAz~aniY","text_ar":"عَازَّنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEazazotuhu","text_ar":"فَعَزَزْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAz~aniY","text_ar":"عَازَّنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he strove with me to overcome, and I overcame him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAz~apN","text_ar":"مُعَازَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contending together in argument:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) you say also of a horse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisahu","text_ar":"فَارِسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtz~","text_ar":"اعتزّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he overcame his rider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gained the mastery over him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmE","text_ar":"جمع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in a prov., (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano Eaz~a baz~a","text_ar":"مَنْ عَزَّ بَزَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who overcomes takes the spoil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K.) And in another prov., (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA Eaz~a A^axuwka fahuno","text_ar":"اـِذَا عَزَّ اَخُوكَ فَهُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, S, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When thy brother overcomes"},{"kind":"text","text":"thee, and thou art not equal to him ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo tuqaAwmohu","text_ar":"لَمْ تُقَاومْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou gentle to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when thy brother magnifies and exalts himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"against thee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abase thyself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA:) or, accord. to Aboo-Is-hák, what Th says is a mistake; the right reading being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahino","text_ar":"فَهِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, and the meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when thy brother is hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to thee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treat thou him with gentleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blandishment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahuno","text_ar":"فَهُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, which is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhawaAnu","text_ar":"الهَوَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but ISd approves and justifies the reading given by Th. (TA.) [See also 10.]       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~ahu","text_ar":"عَزَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~N","text_ar":"عَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~azahu","text_ar":"عَزَّزَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaz~ahu","text_ar":"اَعَزَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) in a sense pointed out below: see 2, in two places. (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,] with the same aor. and inf. n.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"helped, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a AlmaA='u","text_ar":"عَزَّ المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water flowed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~ati AlqaroHapu","text_ar":"عَزَّتِ القَرْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrHp","text_ar":"قرحة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pustule,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discharged what was in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~ato","text_ar":"عَزَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzuwzN","text_ar":"عُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EizaAzN","text_ar":"عِزَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) and , (K,) accord. to IAar, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazuzato","text_ar":"عَزُزَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzuwzN","text_ar":"عُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel, IAar, S, O, K, and a ewe or goat, IAar, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was narrow in the orifices of the teats;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEz~t","text_ar":"اعزّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEz~zt","text_ar":"تعزّزت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazuzato","text_ar":"عَزُزَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is of a very uncommon form, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a","text_ar":"دَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a ewe, or goat,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became scant in her milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKh, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb","text_ar":"لب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","S","A","O","Msb","K","TA","Mgh","Fr","Th","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n28916","headword_ar":"عَزٌّ","root":"Ez","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziyzN","text_ar":"عَزِيزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiYo'a bihi Eaz~FA baz~FA","text_ar":"جِىْءَ بِهِ عَزًّا بَزًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was brought without any means of avoiding it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willingly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against his will:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [as though originally signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by being overcome and despoiled."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n28917","headword_ar":"عِزٌّ","root":"Ez","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Might, potency, power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) and especially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after lowness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanness, of condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓ the latter word: (AZ, S, A, * Msb, and K, in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated, rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state; nobility, honourableness, gloriousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"illustriousness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifoEapN","text_ar":"رِفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ul~N","text_ar":"ذُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, O;) [as also ↓ the latter word: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEiz~iY laqado kaAna ka*aA waka*aA","text_ar":"بِعِزِّى لَقَدْ كَانَ كَذَا وَكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEiz~ika","text_ar":"بِعِزِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By my might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such and such things have happened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEamoriY","text_ar":"لَعَمْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEamoruka","text_ar":"لَعَمْرُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are bad phrases of the people of Esh-Shihr. (TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Self-magnification; self-exaltation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN Aln~afosi","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ النَّفْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: and also,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdainfulness; scornfulness; indignation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a blameable kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur ii. 202. (TA.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power, of resisting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withstanding; resistibility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies the same: and] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of being invincible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not to be overcome:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(B, TA:) and both signify ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impossibility, insuperableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unattainableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rareness; scarceness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of overcoming; conquest; superior power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"farce;"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2032},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~apN","text_ar":"عِزَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) and the latter has this signification especially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to an argumentative contest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTarN Eiz~N","text_ar":"مَطَرٌ عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehement rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copious rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, AHn, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mighty, great, rain, that causes the plain and the mountain to flow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyolN Eiz~N","text_ar":"سِيْلٌ عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An overpowering torrent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","B","K","IAar","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n29027","headword_ar":"عَزٍ","root":"EzY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Patient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enduring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having comely patience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}